(211, 'Capilano University', 'Capilano University is named after Chief Joe Capilano, an important leader of the Squamish Nation of the Coast Salish Peoples. We respectfully acknowledge that our campuses are located on the territories of the LíỈwat, Musqueam,  Sechelt, Squamish and Selilwitulh Nations.', 'Music', '2055 Purcell Way\r\nNorth Vancouver, BC\r\nV7J 3H5', 'advising@capilanou.ca', '604 986 1911', '1', '-', 'CA', 'https://www.capilanou.ca/', 'https://www.capilanou.ca/', 'institutions/1617696278_Capilano.JPG', '2021-04-06 14:04:38', '2021-04-06 14:04:38'),
(212, 'Simon Fraser University', 'SFU has far outgrown the transit that serves it. Without much more robust transit, SFU won’t be able to realize its full potential on Burnaby Mountain. A new gondola will mean Burnaby will continue to benefit from being home to one of Canada’s best research universities.', 'Music', 'Simon Fraser University\r\n8888 University Drive\r\nBurnaby, BC V5A 1S6', 'reginfo@sfu.ca', '7787826930', '1', '-', 'CA', 'https://www.sfu.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/simonfraseruniversity', 'institutions/1617696555_SFU.JPG', '2021-04-06 14:09:15', '2021-04-06 14:09:15'),
(213, 'University of British Columbia', 'Researchers with the CERN-based ALPHA collaboration have announced the world’s first laser-based manipulation of antimatter, leveraging a made-in-Canada laser system to cool a sample of antimatter down to near absolute zero. The achievement, detailed in an article published today and featured on the cover of the journal Nature, will significantly alter the landscape of antimatter research and advance the next generation of experiments.', 'Music', 'Okanagan Campus\r\n3333 University Way\r\nKelowna, BC Canada V1V 1V7', 'admissions.inquiry@ubc.ca', '250 807 8000', '1', '-', 'AF', 'https://www.ubc.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/universityofbc?fref=ts', 'institutions/1617696991_UBC.JPG', '2021-04-06 14:16:31', '2021-04-06 14:16:31'),
(214, 'University of Victoria', 'Dynamic learning, research with a vital impact, and our extraordinary academic environment give UVic an Edge that can’t be found anywhere else.\r\n\r\nThe University of Victoria is one of Canada’s leading research-intensive universities. We are located in Victoria, on the BC coast.', 'Music', 'University of Victoria\r\n3800 Finnerty Road\r\nVictoria BC  V8P 5C2\r\nCanada', 'garo@uvic.ca', '1-250-721-7211', '1', '250-472-4657', 'CA', 'www.uvic.ca', 'https://www.facebook.com/universityofvictoria', 'institutions/1618426940_uvic.PNG', '2021-04-15 01:02:20', '2021-04-15 01:02:20'),
(215, 'Victoria Conservatory of Music', 'A non-profit organization founded in 1964, the Victoria Conservatory of Music (VCM) has earned an outstanding reputation of quality in education, performance, and music therapy. The VCM welcomes the whole community, with students of all ages and musical abilities exploring their creative talents through musical genres from the classical to contemporary and through the use of music technology.', 'Music', 'Victoria Conservatory of Music\r\n900 Johnson Street\r\nVictoria, British Columbia\r\nV8V 3N4', 'info@vcm.bc.ca', '250-386-5311', '1', '250-386-5311', 'CA', 'https://vcm.bc.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/theVCM/?fref=nf', 'institutions/1618427300_victoria conservatory.PNG', '2021-04-15 01:08:20', '2021-04-15 01:08:20'),
(216, 'Vancouver Island University', 'This is a place of acknowledgement and fair access, achievement and personal attention – a special blend of a caring, nurturing environment sets VIU apart from other universities. It’s an essential ingredient for a values-based education that creates an environment balancing academic accomplishments with the goal of developing students\' social and relationship skills to last a lifetime, make a difference, and model others to do the same.', 'Music', 'Nanaimo\r\n(Main Campus)\r\n900 Fifth Street\r\nNanaimo, BC\r\nV9R 5S5\r\nCanada', 'info@viu.ca', '1.250.753.3245', '1', '1.250.753.3245', 'CA', 'https://www.viu.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/viuniversity/', 'institutions/1618428762_viu.PNG', '2021-04-15 01:32:42', '2021-04-15 01:32:42'),
(217, 'Selkirk College', 'Feel at home in our classrooms and communities, nestled within the welcoming West Kootenay and Boundary regions. Since 1966, Selkirk College has been providing innovative and unique learning opportunities.', 'Music', 'British Columbia, Canada', 'communications@selkirk.ca', '1-888-953-1133', '1', '+1 250-365-7292', 'CA', 'https://selkirk.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/SelkirkCollege', 'institutions/1618429074_selkrik.PNG', '2021-04-15 01:37:54', '2021-04-15 01:37:54'),
(218, 'University of Manitoba', 'The University of Manitoba is western Canada’s first university, established in 1877, and located on original lands of Anishinaabeg, Cree, Oji-Cree, Dakota, and Dene peoples, and on the homeland of the Métis Nation. We are Manitoba\'s only research-intensive university, and one of the country’s top research institutions. We have more than 29,000 undergraduate and graduate students, and more than 145,000 alumni living in 140 countries.', 'Music', 'University of Manitoba\r\nWinnipeg, Manitoba, Canada', 'umanitoba@umanitoba.ca', '+1 204-474-8880', '1', '1-800-432-1960', 'CA', 'http://umanitoba.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/umanitoba', 'institutions/1618429484_univmanitoba.PNG', '2021-04-15 01:44:44', '2021-04-15 01:44:44'),
(219, 'Brandon University', 'Success is built at Brandon University. Our growing, progressive campus welcomes a diverse and inclusive community that combines proud tradition with shared ambition.', 'Music', 'Brandon University\r\n270-18th Street\r\nBrandon, Manitoba\r\nR7A 6A9\r\nCANADA', 'communications@brandonu.ca', '+1 204-728-9520', '1', '+1 204-728-9520', 'CA', 'https://www.brandonu.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/BrandonUni', 'institutions/1618430540_brandon.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:02:20', '2021-04-15 02:02:20'),
(220, 'Mount Allison University', 'Mount Allison is ranked Canada\'s #1 undergraduate university by Maclean\'s magazine. Come visit us in Sackville, New Brunswick or check out our virtual tour online. www.mta.ca for more information.', 'Music', 'Mount Allison University\r\nSackville, New Brunswick\r\nCanada E4L 1E4', 'admissions@mta.ca', '+1 506-364-2269', '1', '+1 506-364-2269', 'CA', 'http://www.mta.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/mountallison', 'institutions/1618430818_mountalison.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:06:58', '2021-04-15 02:06:58'),
(221, 'Université de Moncton', 'Université de Moncton, la plus importante université canadienne uniquement de langue française à l’extérieur du Québec. Ses trois campus situés à Edmundston, dans le nord-ouest du Nouveau-Brunswick, à Shippagan, dans le nord-est, et à Moncton, dans le sud-est de la province, offrent une variété de cours dans les arts, les humanités, les sciences pures et appliquées et les sciences sociales.', 'Music', '65 Hébert Boulevard\r\n\r\nEdmundston NB E3V 2S8, Canada', 'info@umce.ca', '506 737-5049', '1', '+1 506-858-4000', 'CA', 'https://www.umoncton.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/umoncton', 'institutions/1618431046_moncton.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:10:46', '2021-04-15 02:10:46'),
(222, 'University of New Brunswick', 'The University of New Brunswick is situated on the traditional territory of the Wolastoqey people. The river that flows beside the university is Wolastoq (beautiful and bountiful river), along which live the Wolastoqiyik (Maliseets).', 'Music', 'New Brunswick\r\nCanada', 'talktous@unb.ca', '1-506-648-5845', '1', '1-506-648-5845', 'CA', 'http://www.unb.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/uofnb', 'institutions/1618431796_unb.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:23:16', '2021-04-15 02:23:16'),
(223, 'Memorial University of Newfoundland', 'At Memorial University more than 19,000 students from over 115 countries come together to discover. From the classics to advanced technology, Memorial offers certificate, diploma, undergraduate, graduate and postgraduate programs across six campuses and online. A global network of almost 100,000 accomplished alumni throughout the world strengthens Memorial University’s capacity and reputation for leadership in research, teaching and public engagement.', 'Music', 'Memorial University of Newfoundland\r\nSt. John\'s, NL A1C 5S7\r\nP.O. Box 4200\r\nCANADA', 'ebruce@mun.ca', '+1 709-864-8000', '1', '+1 709-864-8000', 'CA', 'https://www.mun.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/MemorialUniversity', 'institutions/1618432936_memorial.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:42:16', '2021-04-15 02:42:16'),
(224, 'Acadia University', 'At Acadia University, we’re proud of our family tree. It’s filled with those who have made a difference and made their mark on the world.\r\n\r\nWe trace our roots to 1838, when Baptist leaders reached a breaking point in their ability to access higher education. If they could not become students or teachers at other universities because of their denomination, they would create their own university and remove barriers for themselves and others.', 'Music', 'Acadia University\r\n15 University Avenue\r\nWolfville, Nova Scotia,B4P2R6\r\nCanada', 'agi@acadiau.ca', '902-542-2200', '1', '+1 902-585-2201', 'CA', 'www.acadiau.ca', 'https://www.facebook.com/acadiauniversity', 'institutions/1618433251_acadia.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:47:31', '2021-04-15 02:47:31'),
(225, 'Dalhousie University', 'Dalhousie University is located in Halifax, Nova Scotia which is ranked one of the friendliest cities in the world. Founded in 1818, we\'re one of Canada’s oldest universities, attracting more than 19,000 students from around the world. We make a lasting impact by blending transformative academic programs with pioneering research on Canada’s East Coast.', 'Music', 'Dalhousie University\r\nHalifax, Nova Scotia, Canada  B3H 4R2', 'admissions@dal.ca', '1-902-494-2211', '1', '1-902-494-2211', 'CA', 'www.dal.ca', 'https://www.facebook.com/DalhousieU/', 'institutions/1618433538_dalhousie.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:52:18', '2021-04-15 02:52:18'),
(226, 'Maritime Conservatory of Performing Arts', 'xemplary music & dance classes in Halifax, Nova Scotia. The Maritime Conservatory has been setting the standard for quality education in music and dance for over 130 years. Here individuals of all ages can further their love of dance and music under the guidance of skilled faculty members in a progressive learning environment tailored to match each student’s unique goals.', 'Music', '6199 Chebucto Rd,\r\nHalifax, NS\r\nB3L 1K7', 'admin@maritimeconservatory.com', '902-423-6995', '1', '902-423-6995', 'CA', 'https://maritimeconservatory.com/', 'https://www.facebook.com/maritimeconservatory/', 'institutions/1618433829_conservatory.PNG', '2021-04-15 02:57:09', '2021-04-15 02:57:09'),
(227, 'University of Prince Edward Island', 'Located in Charlottetown, the birthplace of Confederation and the capital city of Prince Edward Island, the University of Prince Edward Island (UPEI) has a rich history with roots in two founding institutions, Prince of Wales College (est. 1834) and Saint Dunstan’s University (est. 1855). Formed in 1969 as the provincial university, UPEI honours its proud legacy through academic excellence and research innovation.', 'Music', '550 University Ave, Charlottetown\r\nPrince Edward Island, Canada C1A 4P3', 'apply@upei.ca', '902-628-4353', '1', '902-628-4353', 'CA', 'https://www.upei.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/UniversityofPEI/', 'institutions/1618434061_prince edward.PNG', '2021-04-15 03:01:01', '2021-04-15 03:01:01'),
(228, 'Brock University', 'Brock is designed to provide students with an outstanding education and relevant employment-related experience. Experience a University for YOU. Come to #BrockU.', 'Music', 'Niagara Region\r\n1812 Sir Isaac Brock Way\r\nSt. Catharines, ON\r\nL2S 3A1 Canada', 'socialmedia@brocku.ca', '+1 905-688-5550', '1', '+1 905-688-5550', 'CA', 'https://brocku.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/brockuniversity', 'institutions/1618434233_brock.PNG', '2021-04-15 03:03:53', '2021-04-15 03:03:53'),
(229, 'Carleton University', 'Welcome to Canada’s capital university.\r\n\r\nSituated on unceded Algonquin territory beside the historic Rideau Canal, an official UNESCO World Heritage Site, Carleton University was founded by the community in 1942 to meet the needs of veterans returning from the Second World War.', 'Music', 'Carleton University\r\n1125 Colonel By Drive\r\nOttawa, Ontario\r\nK1S 5B6 Canada', 'admissions@carleton.ca', '1-613-520-2600', '1', '+1 613-520-7400', 'CA', 'https://carleton.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/carletonuniversity', 'institutions/1618434746_carleton.PNG', '2021-04-15 03:12:26', '2021-04-15 03:12:26'),
(230, 'Hamilton Conservatory for the Arts', 'Hamilton Conservatory for the Arts, located at 126 James Street South in Hamilton, Ontario, offers lessons for all ages and levels. Students at the Conservatory learn dance, singing, acting, visual art, and much more!', 'Music', '126 James Street South, Hamilton, ON L8P 2Z4', 'info@hcarts.ca', '905-528-4020', '1', '905-528-4020', 'CA', 'https://www.hcarts.ca/#', 'https://www.facebook.com/HamiltonConservatory/', 'institutions/1618434922_hca.PNG', '2021-04-15 03:15:22', '2021-04-15 03:15:22'),
(231, 'Humber College', 'Humber emphasizes hands-on, career-focused learning. We offer a broad range of credentials including bachelor\'s degrees, diplomas, certificates and Ontario graduate certificates — and will help you chart the best path towards your goals.', 'Music', '205 Humber College Blvd (10,879.41 km)\r\nM9W 5L7 Toronto, ON, Canada', 'enquiry@humber.ca', '+1 416-675-5000', '1', '+1 416-675-5000', 'CA', 'www.humber.ca', 'https://www.facebook.com/humbercollege', 'institutions/1618435099_hca.PNG', '2021-04-15 03:18:19', '2021-04-15 03:18:19'),
(232, 'McMaster University', 'McMaster University, one of four Canadian universities listed among the Top 100 universities in the world, is renowned for its innovation in both learning and discovery. It has a student population of 30,000, and more than 185,000 alumni in 137 countries.', 'Music', '1280 Main Street West.\r\n \r\nHamilton, Ontario  L8S 4L8.', 'hr.mcmaster@mcmaster.ca', '(905) 525-9140', '1', '(905) 525-9140', 'CA', 'mcmaster.ca', 'https://www.facebook.com/mcmasteruniversity/', 'institutions/1618435406_mcm.PNG', '2021-04-15 03:23:26', '2021-04-15 03:23:26'),
(233, 'Queen\'s University', 'Queen\'s is located in the city of Kingston, Ontario, Canada, half-way between Montreal and Toronto, two of Canada\'s largest cities. Kingston is situated on the shores of Lake Ontario, near the entrance to the St. Lawrence River and Thousand Islands, and the Rideau Canal.', 'Music', 'Kingston,Ontario,Canada', 'social@queensu.ca', '+16135332000', '1', '+16135332000', 'CA', 'http://www.queensu.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/queensuniversity/', 'institutions/1618435620_queens.PNG', '2021-04-15 03:27:00', '2021-04-15 03:27:00');
